---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Calculator from '../components/Calculator.jsx';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Tesla Supercharger Cost per kWh | Voltloop"
  description="Tesla Supercharger pricing explained. Compare Supercharger cost vs home charging and estimate a typical Supercharger session."
>
  <h1>Tesla Supercharger cost</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Tesla Supercharger pricing in the U.S. typically ranges from <strong>$0.25 to $0.50/kWh</strong>,
    averaging around <strong>$0.36/kWh</strong>. Off-peak rates can be 30–50% lower at
    many sites.
  </p>

  <h2>Supercharger vs home charging</h2>
  <table class="compare">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Charging type</th>
        <th>Typical $/kWh</th>
        <th>Cost for 50 kWh</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Home Level 2</td><td>$0.16</td><td>$8.00</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Public Level 2</td><td>$0.20–$0.30</td><td>$10–$15</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Tesla Supercharger</td><td>$0.25–$0.50</td><td>$12.50–$25.00</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Estimate a Supercharger session</h2>
  <p>
    The calculator below is preset for a typical Supercharger road-trip stop: a 75 kWh
    Model 3 going from 10% to 80% at $0.36/kWh.
  </p>

  <Calculator
    client:load
    batterySize={75}
    currentPercent={10}
    targetPercent={80}
    ratePerKwh={0.36}
    chargerType="Supercharger"
  />

  <h2>How to lower Supercharger cost</h2>
  <ul class="related">
    <li>Charge to 80%, not 100% — the last 20% is the slowest and most expensive per minute.</li>
    <li>Use off-peak hours where available (often before 11am and after 9pm).</li>
    <li>Consider a Supercharger membership if you fast-charge frequently.</li>
    <li>Charge at home overnight whenever possible — see the <a href="/ev-charging-cost-calculator">general calculator</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Vehicle-specific examples: <a href="/tesla-model-3-charging-cost">Model 3</a>,
    <a href="/tesla-model-y-charging-cost">Model Y</a>,
    <a href="/tesla-model-s-charging-cost">Model S</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
